---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy | Ollie Pinto"
  description="Plain-English privacy information for Ollie Pinto's personal portfolio and contact form."
  canonicalUrl="https://www.olliepinto.com/privacy"
>
  <Navbar client:load />

  <article class="w-full px-6 pt-36 pb-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-accent-secondary">
        Privacy
      </p>
      <h1 class="mb-6 text-5xl font-serif font-normal text-text-primary md:text-7xl">
        Privacy notice
      </h1>
      <p class="mb-10 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
        This is a personal portfolio for Ollie Pinto. It is designed to share public
        professional information and provide a simple way to get in touch.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-text-primary">
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold">What this site collects</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            If you use the contact form, the site asks for your name, email address,
            and message so Ollie can read and respond to your enquiry. Please avoid
            sending sensitive information through the form.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold">When you send a message</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Messages sent through the contact page are delivered using a third-party
            form service. That service receives the details you submit so the message
            can reach me.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold">Why the information is used</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Contact details are used only to understand your message and reply where
            appropriate. This site does not use those details for analytics, marketing
            lists, or automated profiling.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold">Storage and preferences</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            The site avoids non-essential browser storage on first load. If you choose
            a theme, that preference is stored in your browser so the selected theme can
            be restored on later visits.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold">How long messages are kept</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Messages are kept only for as long as they are useful for replying,
            maintaining context, or handling a legitimate follow-up. Old messages can be
            deleted when they are no longer needed.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold">Getting in touch</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Please use the <a class="font-medium text-text-primary underline decoration-accent-secondary decoration-2 underline-offset-4" href="/contact">contact page</a>
            to send a message about the portfolio or potential work.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
